cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CB 

This paper investigates the relationship between sentence representations learned by deep neural networks and the brain, specifically using magnetoencephalography (MEG) brain recording data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper explores multiple neural network architectures, including ELMo and BERT, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural network representations to generate synthetic brain data, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CB (Computational Biology).
